♪I can't help but be a little bit fragile♪

15
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:44,540
♪I can't help but be a little bit gloomy♪

16
00:01:44,620 --> 00:01:46,980
♪The sky is bright because of you♪

17
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:49,420
♪Without you, the sky is grey♪

18
00:01:49,900 --> 00:01:54,100
♪You are the angel who took away
all of my loneliness♪

19
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:58,060
=Miss Crow With Mr. Lizard=

20
00:01:58,980 --> 00:02:02,060
=Episode 34=

21
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:03,800
If this goes on,

22
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:06,400
what will happen to his mechanical heart?

23
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:11,400
Safe Mode will automatically be activated.

24
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,880
Safe Mode?

25
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,280
(Based on what you told me,)

26
00:02:23,520 --> 00:02:24,920
(Mr. Gu's mechanical heart)

27
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,080
(has already activated)

28
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:27,000
(the safe mode.)

29
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:28,920
(In other words,)

30
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,440
(he can't feel)

31
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,320
(Care instructions, Warning)
any emotions now

32
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:33,360
(Care instructions, Warning)
and it turns him

33
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:37,120
into a vegetable who can still talk and walk.

34
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,040
He might not have

35
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:39,960
any emotions now.

36
00:02:40,200 --> 00:02:41,800
But at least,

37
00:02:41,920 --> 00:02:43,240
it can keep him alive for a while.

38
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:48,000
How long

39
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,800
can his mechanical heart last

40
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,400
if Safe Mode is activated?

41
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,600
It's hard to say.

42
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,680
But all the previous cases

43
00:02:56,920 --> 00:02:58,320
didn't last for more than a year.

44
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:12,740
(After the safe mode is turned on, the usable time
frame is about a year.)

45
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,280
(I think)

46
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,200
(you can look on the bright side.)

47
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:34,480
(At least, now that the safe mode)

48
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,280
(has been activated.)

49
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,400
(It means)

50
00:03:36,600 --> 00:03:38,240
(that he can live a little longer.)

51
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,640
(Perhaps, during this time,)

52
00:03:39,880 --> 00:03:41,600
(other research labs)

53
00:03:41,720 --> 00:03:43,160
(might have come up with new solutions.)

54
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,600
(Don't give up hope.)

55
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,960
(How was your grandma's check-up?)

56
00:04:04,160 --> 00:04:05,680
(Do you want me to pick you up?)

57
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:07,860
♪It takes those I care about♪

58
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:11,420
♪Away from me♪

59
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,500
♪If memory is bright♪

60
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:16,580
♪It would hold up a lamp in my heart♪

61
00:04:16,900 --> 00:04:20,500
♪And light up the night♪

62
00:04:21,100 --> 00:04:36,880
♪Ah~ah~ah~ah~♪

63
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,519
(He can live a little longer.)

64
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,640
(That sounds so cruel.)

65
00:04:42,184 --> 00:04:44,544
(Isn't that a death notice?)

66
00:04:45,280 --> 00:04:46,120
(Dr. Peer's intention)

67
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,360
(of creating this mode)

68
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:48,160
(to help extend)

69
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,720
(the patients' life expectancy.)

70
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:51,640
(At least,)

71
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,200
(they'll have time to say goodbye to the world)

72
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:55,080
(instead of leaving all of a sudden.)

73
00:04:58,260 --> 00:05:02,180
♪If it weren't for parting♪

74
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:06,140
♪How can we meet again♪

75
00:05:07,020 --> 00:05:10,420
♪Ah~ah~♪

76
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:13,420
♪Ah~♪

77
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,540
♪Exchanging sunshine for moonlight♪

78
00:05:39,860 --> 00:05:41,940
♪Exchanging fortune for the past♪

79
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:46,380
♪Exchanging my heartbeat for you♪

80
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,120
How does it feel

81
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,160
to take someone else's money?

82
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:21,800
Why did you suddenly ask that?

83
00:06:23,440 --> 00:06:24,280
I'm just curious.

84
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,520
Was it fun?

85
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,440
Or were there lingering fears

86
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,880
that make you wake up with a start
in the middle of the night?

87
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,400
The latter, of course.

88
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:56,200
Then, I had to face punishment.

89
00:06:57,840 --> 00:06:59,280
After going to jail,

90
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,720
there was endless torment.

91
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:07,080
Regret and guilt.

92
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:09,760
Honestly,

93
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,400
if I were given another chance

94
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:13,640
to choose again,

95
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:14,880
I would never

96
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:17,320
take a dime of anyone's money.

97
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:23,160
I think it's nothing.

98
00:07:24,520 --> 00:07:25,880
Everyone's money is just the same.

99
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:28,560
What you said

100
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,200
is the feeling after being caught.

101
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,960
If you hadn't been arrested

102
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:35,920
and no one came after you

103
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,440
for taking their money,

104
00:07:38,440 --> 00:07:40,360
you wouldn't regret or feel guilty.

105
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,000
Tell me.

106
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:47,000
If I were to follow

107
00:07:47,880 --> 00:07:48,880
in your footsteps,

108
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:49,760
how fun would that be?

109
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,240
What are you talking about?

110
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,800
Why are you yelling?

111
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:58,760
Look, Xiao Xu.

112
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:03,320
Did something happen?

113
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:07,600
If there's anything,

114
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,800
you have to tell me.

115
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:11,120
You don't have to hide it from me, all right?

116
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,440
Yes, I know.

117
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:13,840
All right.

118
00:08:13,920 --> 00:08:15,320
I told you. I was just saying nonsense.

119
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:16,840
Just pretend I didn't say anything.

120
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:17,480
Drink up.

121
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,400
Here.

122
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:21,680
No...

123
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,800
Drink up.

124
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:39,640
Sir.

125
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,800
Sir, where are you going?

126
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,520
Sir, who are you looking for?

127
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:42,280
I'm here for Director Xu.

128
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,760
Sir, you can't go inside.

129
00:08:43,920 --> 00:08:44,480
Sir.

130
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,320
Director Xu, I'm sorry.

131
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,000
I couldn't stop him.

132
00:08:49,840 --> 00:08:51,400
It's so hard to get a chance to meet you.

133
00:08:51,520 --> 00:08:52,360
Director Xu.

134
00:08:52,760 --> 00:08:53,600
Tang.

135
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,240
Long time no see.

136
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:57,159
Long time no see.

137
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,520
Is it that hard to meet me?

138
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,080
Don't say that.

139
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,360
Here. Take a seat.

140
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:02,200
Here.

141
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,679
It was my bad.

142
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,400
Look, now that you're out,

143
00:09:05,560 --> 00:09:06,440
I should have paid you a visit.

144
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,120
But you have to come to me instead.

145
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,480
It's my fault.

146
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,920
I'm here to take some thing.

147
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,560
Take some thing?

148
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,640
What is it?

149
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,200
I'm here to claim

150
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:24,080
what you should have given to me.

151
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,720
I didn't spend ten years in jail

152
00:09:25,880 --> 00:09:26,800
for nothing.

153
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:29,120
You didn't forget

154
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,400
your promise, right?

155
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:33,200
I've kept my promise,

156
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:33,760
Tang.

157
00:09:35,720 --> 00:09:36,800
I raised Tang Xu

158
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,680
and gave him the best life

159
00:09:38,840 --> 00:09:40,000
and the best education.

160
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:42,040
I made him an executive in the company.

161
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,000
Right?

162
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:43,600
So...

163
00:09:44,360 --> 00:09:45,760
What else I didn't do?

164
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:52,040
How dare you bring up Tang Xu?

165
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,240
All these years,

166
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,320
how have you treated him?

167
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,200
Did you think I couldn't tell

168
00:09:59,360 --> 00:10:01,000
how he felt hard done by all these years?

169
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:02,320
Wait.

170
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:04,720
He felt hard done by?

171
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,280
It's me who feels hard done by!

172
00:10:08,640 --> 00:10:09,160
Tang.

173
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:09,760
If you here

174
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:10,760
to talk about this,

175
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:11,320
I...

176
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:12,960
There's nothing to

177
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:13,760
talk about between us.

178
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:24,000
So you're kicking me out?

179
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:27,800
Xu Guo Xiang.

180
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,080
You haven't forgotten what happened

181
00:10:31,880 --> 00:10:32,840
ten years ago, right?

182
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:35,600
Do you need me to remind you?

183
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:44,440
Tang.

184
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,200
Think about it.

185
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:48,640
You're the project manager.

186
00:10:49,080 --> 00:10:49,760
You can't get away

187
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:51,240
with it anyway.

188
00:10:53,040 --> 00:10:54,400
But have you thought about it?

189
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:57,000
If you're put behind bars,

190
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,840
what's going to happen to your wife and kid?

191
00:10:59,120 --> 00:10:59,920
I heard that your wife

192
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:00,960
does not have a permanent job

193
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,480
and your son is still young.

194
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:05,040
How are they going to live? Have you
thought about that?

195
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:09,520
Just keep me out of it.

196
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,960
Even if you're put behind bars,

197
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,360
it'll just be a few years.

198
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:14,520
I'll take care

199
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:15,360
of your wife and son.

200
00:11:15,560 --> 00:11:16,360
I'll send your son

201
00:11:16,440 --> 00:11:17,720
to college, to study abroad,

202
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,320
and even make him a shareholder.

203
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,160
It's all on me.

204
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,040
It's just a few years.

205
00:11:33,680 --> 00:11:34,360
Tang.

206
00:11:35,360 --> 00:11:36,040
No problem.

207
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:37,560
I can promise you that.

208
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,760
This amount of money

209
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,520
isn't a big deal.

210
00:11:41,440 --> 00:11:43,600
I can give you twice the amount.

211
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:45,280
But...

212
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:48,680
not anymore.

213
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,320
Because your Tang Xu

214
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,240
was such a disappointment. Do you know that?

215
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,280
But because

216
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,720
he's your son,

217
00:11:54,840 --> 00:11:55,800
I let things slide.

218
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,720
But I have a record here.

219
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:00,960
Take a look.

220
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:02,880
That will get him decades of imprisonment.

221
00:12:12,660 --> 00:12:15,380
(Jiangdong Commercial Bank, Personal account
transaction details)

222
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:26,840
Xu Guo Xiang, you're a scumbag.

223
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:28,080
You're obviously

224
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:29,160
using Tang Xu!

225
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,360
How dare you...

226
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:34,080
Let go of me!

227
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:37,480
Don't move.

228
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,120
Tang.

229
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:47,760
I just don't get it.

230
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,440
You're not young anymore.

231
00:12:50,240 --> 00:12:51,640
Why are you still so impulsive?

232
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,320
And you're so brainless.

233
00:12:55,240 --> 00:12:57,560
If I don't have something on Tang Xu,

234
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,200
do you think I can trust you?

235
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,280
Listen up, Xu Guo Xiang!

236
00:13:04,200 --> 00:13:05,960
If you dare to hurt Tang Xu,

237
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:07,800
I'll fight you till the end!

238
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:11,640
Assistant Liu.

239
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,920
He's too noisy. Throw him out.

240
00:13:15,240 --> 00:13:15,880
Move.

241
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:17,640
Move.

242
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:20,400
I won't spare you!

243
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,080
A mad dog.

244
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:45,960
What should I do?

245
00:13:46,440 --> 00:13:48,480
I miss you so much and it's only been a day.

246
00:13:50,400 --> 00:13:52,240
Why didn't you reply to my message yesterday?

247
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,960
I miss you so much

248
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:58,600
that words alone

249
00:13:58,720 --> 00:13:59,720
can't express how I feel.

250
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,160
How was Grandma's check-up?

251
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:04,400
It was good.

252
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,800
As usual. It's just her dementia.

253
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:17,320
What's wrong?

254
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,320
Nothing.

255
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:22,840
I'm just hungry.

256
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,920
What would you like to eat? I'll cook for you.

257
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:32,560
So you still care about me.

258
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:35,240
Why would you say that?

259
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:39,360
I used to be the one who cooked for you.

260
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:43,040
From now on, I'll cook for you.

261
00:14:44,840 --> 00:14:45,920
What would you like to eat?

262
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:50,880
I love anything

263
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:52,040
that you make.

264
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:53,040
Really?

265
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,160
I...

266
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:18,520
You go first.

267
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,280
How about taking a walk

268
00:15:22,720 --> 00:15:23,880
after dinner?

269
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:26,600
Where to? Is it far?

270
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,680
Just around here.

271
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:33,400
Okay, I'll go with you.

272
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:42,400
I have something to tell you.

273
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:00,360
Let's eat.

274
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:02,840
I'll try the soup that you made.

275
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:10,440
(It looks like)

276
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:11,840
(the safe mode has been activated.)

277
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,600
(Is it going to end like this?)

278
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,280
(Stop trying out anything,)

279
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:17,920
(will you?)

280
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,360
(Let things stay the same they are)

281
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:21,960
(and it's good enough already.)

282
00:16:38,440 --> 00:16:40,080
Why did you bring me here?

283
00:16:41,520 --> 00:16:42,800
Just feel like coming here.

284
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:45,000
Did you forget this place?

285
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:50,360
My book!

286
00:16:54,400 --> 00:16:54,800
Thank you.

